===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|NL.|academia}}, from {{der|en|grc|Ἀκαδημία}}; see {{m|en|academy}}. ''Academe'' (frequently capitalized) is a poetic name for the garden or grove near ancient Athens where {{w|Plato}} taught, supposedly named for its former owner, the hero Ἀκάδημος (''{{w|Akademos}};'' Ἑκάδημος, ''Hekademos'').

